    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-25T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-25T20:00:00-05:00" n="332"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d332">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112A European War, 1939/4094:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-25T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 25, 1941—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 26—1:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>581. Since there have been several instances of imports into Colombia on Dutch
                    ships from Brazil and Argentina by firms on Proclaimed List the Department might
                    care to enlist the cooperation of the Netherlands to instruct their shipping
                    companies not to accept cargo for proclaimed firms.<note n="42" xml:id="d332fn1"
                        >In Department’s telegram No. 489, December 11, 8 p.m., the Ambassador In
                        Colombia was informed that the matter had been discussed with
                        representatives of the Netherlands Legation and that they had agreed to have
                        instructions sent out to remedy the situation (740.00112A European War,
                        1939/4094).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Braden</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
